\f15\b0 \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Three categories, one flow:\

\f16\b Deployment (purple) \'97 what the solver actually decides.
\f15\b0  Only 
\f17\fs26 x_\{i,z,t,p\}
\f15\fs24  is a real decision: commit to a type, zone, slot, and persona simultaneously or don't. 
\f17\fs26 x_\{i,t\}
\f15\fs24  is just a collapsed view of it \'97 zone and persona are erased so C4 can check whether two conflicting types are both active in the same slot. It carries no independent information; it exists purely to simplify one constraint check.\

\f16\b Discovery state (amber) \'97 what the attacker learns over time.
\f15\b0  Two independent burn clocks run silently in the background from the moment a deployment goes live. 
\f17\fs26 u_\{i,z,t\}
\f15\fs24  tracks how long the same service type has been visible in a zone \'97 when it hits \uc0\u964 
\f13 \uc0\u7496 
\f15  consecutive slots, the type is burned and no persona change can save it. 
\f17\fs26 u_\{i,z,t,p\}
\f15\fs24  tracks how long the same persona identity has been visible \'97 when it hits \uc0\u964 
\f13 \uc0\u7496 \u7510 
\f15  consecutive slots, that specific identity is burned, but rotating to a new persona resets it independently. Both flags gate credit: either fires 
\f13 \uc0\u8594 
\f15  zero, regardless of everything else.\

\f16\b Coverage outcome (teal) \'97 what earns credit.
\f15\b0  Three variables form a strict chain. 
\f17\fs26 c_\{j,a,t\}
\f15\fs24  is the detection event \'97 only fires if a real, undiscovered deployment is present (both burn flags zero). 
\f17\fs26 p_\{\uc0\u960 ,h,t\}
\f15\fs24  is hop coverage \'97 only true if a detection fires in the right zone at the right slot. 
\f17\fs26 e_\{\uc0\u960 ,t\}
\f15\fs24  is early interception \'97 only true if a non-final hop is covered, which earns the L4 prevention bonus (1000\'d7 over forensic credit). Each step in the chain requires the one below it to be true first.\
The dashed line from Deployment to Coverage outcome at the bottom of the diagram captures the key dependency: 
\f17\fs26 x=1
\f15\fs24  is necessary but not sufficient \'97 both discovery flags must also be zero. The solver's continuous pressure to rotate both type and persona comes directly from knowing that either burn flag silently zeroes the entire credit chain above it.\
