\f16 \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Why geometric weights, not arbitrary ones.
\f15\b0  The ratios are 10\'d7, 100\'d7, 1000\'d7 between adjacent levels \'97 not 2\'d7 or 5\'d7. This is the mathematical guarantee that no accumulation of lower-level credits can substitute for one unit of the next level up. A million L1 detections still equals exactly one L4 early interception. The solver cannot trade its way up the hierarchy \'97 it must genuinely satisfy higher-priority clauses.\

\f16\b L4 (1000\'d7 weight) \'97 prevention is the only thing that matters at the top.
\f15\b0  The max over all non-final hops is what distinguishes L4 from L3-fwd: it rewards the single best early-hop placement on the path, not all of them. The 1000\'d7 multiplier means the solver will always sacrifice any amount of forensic, technique, or detection credit to gain one early interception.\

\f16\b L3-fwd vs L3-bwd \'97 same structure, one number different.
\f15\b0  The 0.7 factor on L3-bwd is the forensic discount. Detection at the final hop has genuine value \'97 it produces attribution evidence, logs the technique, enables incident response. But the target was already reached. The 0.7 keeps forensic coverage in the objective without letting it crowd out prevention placements.\

\f16\b L2-tech and L2-fam \'97 spreading not deepening.
\f15\b0  Both clauses award a bonus only for something new: a technique not yet covered anywhere, or a tactic family not yet represented. Double-covering an already-monitored technique earns nothing extra. The 1.2\'d7 on L2-fam over L2-tech means spanning a new kill-chain stage \'97 Initial Access, Lateral Movement, Exfiltration \'97 is worth slightly more than adding another technique within a stage already covered. This prevents the solver from going infinitely deep into Lateral Movement while leaving Exfiltration completely dark.\

\f16\b L1 \'97 the floor that makes every deployment count.
\f15\b0  Even a honeypot that cannot contribute to path coverage, technique breadth, or tactic families still earns detection credit. No placement is ever completely worthless to the solver. This matters because it keeps the solver considering low-probability nodes that might catch opportunistic activity.\

\f16\b The q
\f5\b0 \uc0\u8346 
\f16\b  and dual guards \'97 the persona extension in three factors.
\f15\b0  Every clause above carries three extra multipliers. q
\f5 \uc0\u8346 
\f15  scales the credit by how attractive this persona is to the current threat actor \'97 set by the LLM from STIX intelligence, not hardcoded. (1\uc0\u8722 u_type) and (1\u8722 u_persona) are the kill switches: binary, not soft. Either guard firing drops the entire product to zero. The solver internalises this and treats stagnating type or persona as a liability that silently drains credit from every clause in the objective simultaneously.\
