\f16 \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 The six objectives are a covering set over attacker evasion strategies.
\f15\b0  Each one closes a channel the others cannot. O1 closes spatial evasion \'97 a solver without it would deploy in zero-traffic zones. O2 closes technique evasion \'97 an attacker who knows which ATT&CK techniques are unmonitored will use exactly those. O3 closes tactic-family evasion \'97 an attacker blocked in Lateral Movement simply pivots to Initial Access or Exfiltration. O4 closes the prevention\'96forensics confusion \'97 without the 1000\'d7 weight, the solver cannot distinguish catching the attacker at hop 1 from recording them at the final hop. O5 ensures forensic coverage is retained but explicitly discounted. O6 closes the greedy blindness \'97 a solver evaluating paths one at a time never discovers that one deployment covers many paths simultaneously.\

\f16\b The six dimensions are the structural mechanisms that make each objective inviolable.
\f15\b0  D1 makes zone a first-class index \'97 without it the solver cannot enforce zone budgets or air-gap isolation. D2 encodes time and hop order \'97 without it the solver cannot distinguish early from late detection or eliminate temporal gaps. D3 adds explicit technique and family breadth objectives \'97 without it, optimising path weights alone produces deep narrow coverage. D4 makes budget and conflict constraints hard \'97 without it they are soft preferences the solver can trade away. D5 gives an optimality certificate \'97 without it you have a heuristic that cannot prove it found the best plan. D6 makes persona a first-class variable \'97 without it the type-rotation defence is bypassed at the identity layer.\

\f16\b D2 and D3 address orthogonal failure modes of the same base system.
\f15\b0  A deployment with perfect D2 and zero D3 is vulnerable to any attacker who switches technique \'97 the timing is airtight but the coverage matrix has holes. A deployment with perfect D3 and zero D2 is vulnerable to any attacker who waits for a temporal gap \'97 every technique is covered but not every month. Both are required. Neither implies the other.\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

