\f15\b0\fs24 \cf0 These ten parameters are the newest and most distinctive part of the formulation. Everything before this \'97 the network inventory, the attack picture, the constraints, the value adjustments \'97 existed in some form in prior honeypot placement work. The persona layer is what makes this formulation different.\
The central insight is simple: 
\f16\b attackers do not just identify honeypot types, they map identities
\f15\b0 . A patient attacker does not think "there is an SSH server at 10.2.3.45." They think "Alice Smith's HR workstation has been at 10.2.3.45 for three months \'97 I know its hostname, its AD account, its SSL certificate, its login schedule, and its network neighbors." Changing the SSH service does nothing against this attacker. Only changing the identity \'97 the complete package of hostname, account, certificate, and behavior \'97 forces them to restart their reconnaissance from scratch.\
The persona layer gives the solver the parameters it needs to plan, execute, and continuously adapt an identity-rotation schedule across a multi-month horizon.\
