\f16\b \cf0 Why \uc0\u916 
\f5\b0 \uc0\u8346 
\f16\b  exists and why it is separate from \uc0\u916 :
\f15\b0 \
Persona changes are cheaper than type rotations \'97 no software reinstallation, no monitoring gap, no full reconfiguration. But they still cost engineer time: create the new AD account, issue the new certificate, configure the new hostname and DNS record, update the traffic simulation pattern, test the new identity for plausibility, and notify the monitoring team.\
Each persona change takes approximately two to three hours. With \uc0\u916 
\f5 \uc0\u8346 
\f15  = 2 and H = 4 months, the team handles at most two persona changes per honeypot per zone across the entire quarter \'97 roughly one change every other month on the most active honeypots. This is manageable.\

