\f16\b \cf0 Why q
\f5\b0 \uc0\u8346 
\f16\b  is a stronger LLM contribution than adjusting anonymous weights:
\f15\b0 \
When Algorithm 1 outputs updated q
\f5 \uc0\u8346 
\f15  values, the security team receives an operationally interpretable directive: "This month, prioritize Finance_DB and HR_workstation personas." A security analyst can read that, understand it, debate it, and override it if domain knowledge warrants.\
If Algorithm 1 instead output updated w
\f19 \uc0\u11388 
\f15  values \'97 "increase w_\{T1048\} from 0.90 to 0.95" \'97 the analyst has no way to evaluate whether that adjustment is correct without understanding the full weight formula and its interactions. The q
\f5 \uc0\u8346 
\f15  output is transparent. The w
\f19 \uc0\u11388 
\f15  output is opaque.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
